 # Spike: site crawling with robots.txt respect and conservative rate limiting
 
-
+The web-fetch PRD explicitly tabled site crawling (scope 2) with the note 'ethical concerns — LLM crawling is contentious. Would need robots.txt respect, conservative rate limiting. No personal need identified.'
+
+This ticket exists to capture that explicit deferral so a future decision to implement or formally WONTFIX is tracked rather than lost.
+
+## What crawling would look like
+
+Given a starting URL, crawl pages up to a configurable depth or page count, respecting:
+- `robots.txt` at the domain root
+- configurable rate limiting (min delay between requests)
+- optional domain restriction (stay on the same domain)
+- deduplicated URLs
+
+Return: a list of fetched+extracted pages, or stream them as discovered.
+
+## References
+
+- `.sandpiper/docs/web-fetch-prd.md` — Deferred capabilities, Scope 2
+- WEB-11 — search tool (would be a natural companion to crawling for research workflows)
